This data was generated using Grok.  Asked for a prompt for future use, Grok responded with something similar to this:

Provide a comprehensive list of every significant event in the Bible Book of [BOOK NAME], with the following strict requirements:

• Do not combine separate narrative moments into a single entry; break events into the smallest logical, distinct units that still represent meaningful actions, speeches, divine interventions, or transitions in the text.
• Describe each event using exactly one complete, grammatically correct sentence written in the present tense or simple past tense as appropriate to the narrative style.
• Output a table with two columns: Verse Range, and Event Description.
• In the Verse Range column, include the book name followed by the precise chapter and verse range (e.g., [BOOK NAME] 1:1–5).
• Ensure the list covers the entire book from beginning to end without omission of any major or minor narrative development.
• Strictly maintain the order of the events as they occur in the text.
• Do not include introductory or concluding commentary outside the table; present only the table.
• The final sentence of your response should read exactly: “This list contains [total number] distinct events, fully covering the entire narrative of the Book of [BOOK NAME].”

